An '''anchor portal''' or '''H-frame tower''' is a [[wikt:gantry|gantry]] structure supporting [[overhead power line]]s in a [[Electrical substation|switchyard]]. Their static function is similar to a [[dead-end tower]]. Anchor portals are almost always [[steel]]-tube or steel-framework constructions.
