'''Soilon''' is a fine mesh made from poly lactic acid (PLA) polymer resin by lactic fermentation of glucose, derived from starch (such as [[corn starch]]), by an enzyme and polymerization. By thermal polymerizing of lactic acid, an aliphatic polyester resin having melting point of 170 C and 57C second order transition point respectively is gotten. Due to its plastic character, PLA can be melt-spun into fibers (filaments), which are woven for beverage filter media. It was designed for (and often used in) [[teabag]]s.  It was chosen to replace the materials in teabags, since it can be [[Biodegradation|biodegraded]] and broken down readily by [[microorganism]]s in the soil.  It is a safe and non-toxic alternative to the paper bags usually employed.

